  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advancing NGO Evaluation Practice and Strengthening Local M&amp;E Capacity through Innovative Partnerships</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to advance evaluation practice and its prioritization among InterAction members; to support the development of local, in-country monitoring and evaluation (M&amp;E) capacity; and to promote broader NGO contributions to the field of development evaluation, with a focus on bottom-up approaches. Activities undertaken under this project include a workshop for managers of impact evaluation; a workshop on evaluative thinking; a publication on evaluative thinking featuring four case studies; and the development of a briefing paper and how-to guidance on promoting local ownership in evaluation.</narrative>
  </description>
